ime the sum and difference of the hypotenuse and base, G, and C, are single squares. In the \"doubling\" process, the double of a single square is a double square, but the doubling of a double square is a single square. This, in effect, reverses the position of D and E, with A and B. Then such a triangle is considered to be rotated through ninety degrees.\n\nBut the \"doubling\" process is not particularly a mathematical doubling. In fact it has nothing to do with doubling. In this doubling process the ellipticity of the ellipse is actually drastically changed. All ellipses fall on one side or the other of the basic ellipse which begins with the roots, 1, 1, 2, 3, which are in turn, representative of the 3, 4, 5, Prime Pythagorean triangle. When an ellipse or triangle have roots which are near to this value the doubling process causes little change. One side will have ellipses slightly more circular. The other side of this median will have ellipses slightly more elongated.\nIf this \"doubling\" (see DOUBLING) concept has a reality and an application it would be in the case of the correlation between Earth orbit and the orbit of Halleys Comet. Note that the quantum numbers for them 1, 29, 30, 59, and 59, 1, 60, 61. This combination indicates that Halleys Comet has some special relationship with Earth. The \"59\" used as roots in both cases indicates a close synchronization between them, and the \"1\" in each case indicates a highly stabilized orbit, for each of them.\nTangent Functions\nTangent functions are represented with F/C.\nThe Laws of One (QA)\nThe Laws of One (QA)\nThe Laws of One (QA)\n(click to enlarge)\n\nTHE ONE is composed of two squares: One male, one female. They break into 3 rectangles, C, J \u0026 K, and into 3 more squares, A, B \u0026 E.\n\nCapital letters are areas. Lower case are distances. b+e\u003dd, e+d\u003da.\nIn this case b\u003d3; e\u003d1; d\u003d4; a\u003d5. There may be other coprime values.\nTrigonometric Functions\nTrigonometric func